text: A chain convenience store, Cheers is an exceptionally well stocked store with a great variety of international Asian foods (Malay, Thai, Singaporean, Japanese..).  It includes freshly cut fruits, drinks, chips, crackers, instant ramen, wine, travel necessities including very reasonable prices on electrical adapters, and many other things to fill your basket.

Met an extremely polite and well mannered Indian lady just now in the morning, it starts my day well! Singapore definitely needs a lot more of people and services like this, it’s my first time ever experiencing such nice and courteous service in Singapore (and u know the whole sg don’t have service tbh) and I hope this encourage more!
Had a bad and unfriendly incident with cashier Wanii this morning. Reason being is because I can't afford it and hence she gave me a face and an attitude 👎. Happened at around 9am (28/1/23)
It's expensive. Buy it at the supermarket on the second basement floor of Jewel Changi. You can buy good, cheap food in just a 5-minute walk.
